1. e4 g6 { The Modern Defense! You know what to do by now against these hypermodern systems... } 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 (3. Nf3 { This is a good alternative, now play 3.Nc3 }) 3... b6 { A new move for us, but we know the idea already - Black wants to play a Hippo setup with ...Bb7 and later ...e6/...Ne7/...d6/...Nd7 in some order. What might we do about that? } 4. h4 (4. Nf3 { This is good too, but my suggestion of 4.h4 gives us a clearer attacking plan }) (4. Be3 { This is good too, but my suggestion of 4.h4 gives us a clearer attacking plan }) (4. f4 { Also playable but I've recommended 4.h4 as a more direct attacking approach }) 4... Bb7 { Black should probably have played 4...h5 instead - can you show why? } 5. h5 { We have a great attack on the kingside already and Black can't just castle short as ...Nf6 runs into h6 and ...e6/...Ne7 also will run into h6 - the thorn pawn showing its claws! } { [%csl Gh6][%cal Gh5h6,Gh5g6] } *


